title: The Grissom Gang (1971)
description:
An underrated gem by non other than Mr. Robert Aldrich. This was the last film to be produced by his own production company (Associates & Aldrich) and at his own studio (bought with incomes from his biggest hit, 'The Dirty Dozen'), before he was forced to sell  it after a series of commercial flops.

According to IMDB, full running time is 128 minutes, but this one only runs 123, so it is possibly cut. I am unaware of its origin (wether some old, impossible-to-find VHS copy, more recent DVD or other release).


Starring: Scott Wilson, Kim Darby, Irene Daily, Tony Musante, Ralph Waite and Robert Lansing among others.
